Load Data into Reference tables 11


 

1.      Create Reference or Dictionary Tables for all the dimensions – Model, PaintColor, Region, VehicleType, Manufacturer, State, Condition and TitleStatus:

a.        Click on the PackageLoadODS_ReferenceTbls.dtsx Package to get onto the design canvas

 

b.        Drag and drop a Data Flow Task and rename it as Data Flow Task-LoadDictionariesODS and double click in it to get into edit

 

c.        Drag and drop OLE DB data source and double click it to edit. Connect to the final CraigsList Table dbo.CraigsListSTGf in staging area and select the above dimension columns as in below screenshot:


d.        Drag and drop a Multicast Transformation onto the canvas and drop the precedence constraint from the OEL DB Source above to it.


e.        Drag and drop the Aggregate Transformation and drop a precedence constraint to it from above.  Double click it to configure.  Select Model and Manufacturer columns as they are related. See below screenshot.


f.        Drag and drop the Lookup Transformation onto the canvas. Drop the precedence constraint to it from above. Double click to configure by matching Manufacture and Model from source with the same from the Model table to ensure no duplicates by redirecting to Lookup No Match Output. See screenshot below:


g.        Drag and drop OLE DB Destination Transformation onto the canvas and drop the Lookup No Match precedence constraint onto it. Connect to the destination table, dbo.Model, using connection manager and map the columns as shown in screenshot below:


2.      Repeat steps (a) to (g)  above for the rest of the dimension columns above.



3.      Update Model table with ManufacturerID as they are related:

a.        Drag and drop a Data Flow Task onto the canvas at the Package level and rename it as Data Flow Task-ModelODS.  Double click it to get into the Data Flow Task design.

b.        Drag and drop OLE DB Source and double click it to configure with source as dbo.Manufacturer and select the columns as ManufacturerID and Manufacturer.  See below screenshot:

 


c.        Drag and drop Lookup Transformation onto the canvas and drop precedence constraint from above onto it.  Double click to configure as below to match the ManufacturerName column source to the Model table ManufacturerName column to avoid new records which have not been inserted.


d.        Drag and drop OLE DB Command Transformation onto the canvas for updating.  Rename the object as OLE DB Command-Update ModelTbl with ManufacturerID.  Drop the Lookup Match Output precedence constraint onto it.  Double click it to configure as below screenshot:

o   Provide (1) the connection manager, (2) the T-SQL update script in SSIS format with parameters, and (3) map the parameters to the relevant columns.



4.      Update Region table with StateID as they are related:


a.        Repeat for the process as in the previous process for (3) above - Update Model table with ManufacturerID as they are related.
